To download the required libraries do this in the terminal:
pip install -r requirements.txt
Afterwards, to run the task 1 code, run:
python extract_cnn_features_task1.py
python extract_extra_features_task1.py
python train_task1.py
This will run task 1 in its entirety. This should output results into the terminal, as well as into the outputs and figures folder in the same directory
extract_cnn_features_task1.py will output cnn_features.csv
extract_extra_features_task1.py will output extra_features.csv
train_task1.py will output the classification reports for all three models and the best option in classification_report_(best/logreg/rf/svm_rbf).txt
It will also output all the Cross validation results for the models in cv_results.csv, as well as the Kaggle format submisson in task1_submission.csv
In a different folder in the same drectory called figures, train_task1.py will output accuracy_comparison.png, confusion_logreg.png, confusion_matrix_best.png, confusion_rf.png and confusion_svm_sbf.png

To run the task 2 code, run:
python extract_cnn_features_task2.py
python extract_extra_features_task2.py
python train_task2.py
This will run task 2 in its entirety. This should output results into the terminal, as well as into the outputs and figures folder in the same directory
extract_cnn_features_task2.py will output cnn_features_task2.csv
extract_extra_features_task2.py will output extra_features_task2.csv
train_task2.py will output the classification reports for all three models and the best option in classification_report_(best/logreg/rf/svm_rbf)_task2.txt
It will also output all the Cross validation results for the models in cv_results_task2.csv, as well as the Kaggle format submisson in task2_submission.csv
In a different folder in the same drectory called figures, train_task2.py will output accuracy_comparison_task2.png, confusion_logreg.png_task2, confusion_matrix_best_task2.png, confusion_rf_task2.png and confusion_svm_sbf_task2.png

